post_text:
Proof of a dental exam within the past 18 months is required for all Kindergarten, 2nd grade, and 6th grade students. Forms need to be turned into the school nurse by May 15, 2019. If your child has not had a dental exam in the past 18 months and is enrolled in Kdg, 2nd, or 6th grade, please contact the school nurse to discuss the option of a dental waiver.

Starting for the 2019-2020 school year, all 9th grade students will be required to submit proof of a dental exam. The exam needs to have been completed between the dates of November 15, 2018 to May 15, 2020. You dentist can fax the completed forms to the Carterville High School at 618-985-2741.

post_text:
It's time to start scheduling school physicals for the 2019-2020 school year. School physicals are required for students entering Pre-K, Kindergarten, 6th grade, and 9th grade. Kindergarten physicals are due by the first day of school. 6th and 9th grade physicals are due by October 15th, 2019.

Immunizations are required to be up to date per the Illinois Department of Public Health requirements.
You may submit your completed physicals and immunization records to the school nurse at any time.
